title: Excitation Functions and Thick Target Yields For Radioisotopes Induced in Natural Mg, Co, Ni and Ta By Medium Energy Protons

x4freetext: Excitation Functions and Thick Target Yields For
Radioisotopes Induced in Natural Mg, Co, Ni and Ta
By Medium Energy Protons

x4codes.hlp: National Physical Research Lab., Pretoria, South Africa, Rep.
Catholic Univ. of Louvain, Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium

x4freetext: .Laboratoire De Chimie Nucleaire

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.28, p.533 (1977)

x4codes.hlp: University of Maryland, College Park, MD, United States of America

x4freetext: Used For a Preliminary Bombardment of a Single Stack
Containing Foils of Mg, Co, Ni and Ta with 100 MeV
Protons.

x4codes.hlp: Catholic Univ. of Louvain, Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium

x4freetext: Used For Three Bombardments of Stacks Containing Foils
Of Mg, Co, Ni and Ta with 85 MeV Protons and For
Bombarding Thick Targets of Mg and Co.
As Experimentally Shown Recoil Losses Where Less Than
0.3%. No Corrections were Therefore Made For this
Effect. Corrections For the Attenuation of the Proton
Beam Intensity were Calculated by Making Use of
Experimentally Determined Total Cross Sections.
The Overall Uncertainties in the Cross Sections are
Estimated to be Between 6 and 9 %. They are Based on
Estimated Systematic Errors, Reproducibility of the
Results and Uncertainties in the Various Parameters
Used For the Calculations.
Data Given by the Author in
Nanocurie/Microampere-Hour Per Milligram/Centimeter**2,
Thus Referring to the Produced Radioactivity Rather
Than to a Specific Reaction.  This was done, Since Most
Of the Activities are Produced Via Several Reactions.
Lakw
Some Corrections have Been Included by
CAJAD
Lower Case. Some Reaction Lines are
Corrected
Subentry 011 is Corrected.
Last checking has been done.
The Thick Target Yield, Presented As Curve, was
Obtained by Numerical Integration of the Experimental
Excitation Function.
Energy Degradation in the Stack was Calculated
According to C.F.Williamson Et Al.,Cea-R3042(1966)
Rods of Natural Mg, Chemical Purity Better Than 99.9
%, Thickness 3800, 5700 and 7900 Mg/Cm**2 For Thick
Target Yields at 55, 70 and 85 MeV, Respectively.
Three Stacks Each Consisting of Foils of the Following
Natural Elements For Which Thicknesses in Mg/Cm**2 and
Chemical Purities are Given in Parentheses
Ni (220, 99.99%), Ta (250, 99.95%). The Sequence of the
Four Elements was Changed in Replicate Stacks So As to
Spread the Cross Sections More Evenly Over the Energy
Range Involved. Apart from the Target Foils No Other
Degrader or Catcher Foils were Employed in the Stacks.
Measured by Comparison with a Standard Na-22 Solution.
The Cross Sections in Nci/Muahr Per Mg/Cm**2 were
Obtained As Numerical Values from F.J.Haasbroek.
The Cross Sections in Mb were Calculated by the
Compiler of Kachapag by Multiplying these Values with
The Factor 7.899.
Values at 40, 55, 70, 85 and 100 MeV are Given
Numerically in the Second Reference.
